				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$${\mathrm{Ga}}_{\mathrm{i}}^{2 + }$$\end{document} defects remain spin polarized during the time when CB electrons undergo spin relaxation. Whenever that happens, the defects will immediately filter out these spin-flipped CB electrons as long as their capture time by the defects (τnr) is shorter than the CB electron spin relaxation time τs. As τnr is typically in the order of ps, the spin filtering and spin amplification can be accomplished within a very short time. The efficiency of the SDR and DSP processes can also be accelerated by increasing circularly polarized light intensity because it is accompanied by an increasing probability of the Gai2+\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
